This paper deals with the analysis of mobile traffic patterns in a metropolitan city, which involves the processing of large-scale traffic measurement data and the modeling of traffic patterns. This work is related to the field of network infrastructure (NI) and system and information theory (SI) as it deals with the analysis of cellular towers and their traffic patterns. Additionally, the paper addresses the challenges of urban ecology and human behavior, which are relevant to the field of cybernetics (CY). The paper also proposes a model for traffic pattern extraction and analysis, which is related to the field of cryptography and security (CR) and systems and control (SY).
